text.en: (2.01) Was proof of classification made available to the inspector upon request? (2.2.1(1) & 2.2.1(2) TDGR)
text.fr: (2.01) Une preuve de classification a-t-elle été fournie à l'inspecteur sur demande? (2.2.1(1) & (2) RTMD)

text.en: (2.01a) Does the proof of classification contain all the required information? (2.2.1(3) TDGR)
text.fr: (2.01a) La preuve de classification contient-elle toutes les informations requises? (2.2.1(3) RTMD)

text.en: (2.01b) Has the consignor properly classified the dangerous goods? (2.2 - 2.43.1, except 2.2.1 TDGR)
text.fr: (2.01b) L'expéditeur a-t-il correctement classé les marchandises dangereuses? (2.2 - 2.43.1, sauf 2.2.1 RTMD)

text.en: (3.01) Are the dangerous goods accompanied by a shipping document? (3.1 - 3.2 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01) Les marchandises dangereuses sont-elles accompagnées d'un document d'expédition? (3.1 - 3.2 RTMD)

text.en: (3.01a) Does the shipping document contain all required information and is legible? (3.4 - 3.6.1 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01a) Le document d'expédition contient-il toutes les informations requises et est-il lisible? (3.4-3.6.1 RTMD)

text.en: (3.01b) Is the shipping document kept in the correct location? (3.7 & 3.9 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01b) Le document d'expédition est-il conservé au bon emplacement ? (3.7 & 3.9 RTMD)

text.en: (3.01c) Is the shipping document located in the appropriate place while the dangerous goods are stored in the course of transportation? (3.10 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01c) Le document d'expédition est-il situé à lemplacement approprié pendant que les marchandises dangereuses sont entreposées au cours du transport? (3.10 RTMD)

text.en: (3.01d) Are shipping documents kept for two years? (s. 3.11 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01d) Les documents d'expédition sont-ils conservés pendant deux ans ? (a. 3.11 RTMD)

text.en: (3.02) Are the dangerous goods accompanied by a consist? (3.3(1) & 3.4(1) TDGR)
text.fr: (3.02) Les marchandises dangereuses sont-elles accompagnées d'une feuille de train? (3.3(1) & 3.4(1) RTMD)

text.en: (3.02a) Does the consist contain all required information? (3.3(2) & 3.4(1) TDGR)
text.fr: (3.02a) La feuille de train contient-elle toutes les informations requises? (3.3(2) & 3.4(1) RTMD)

text.en: (3.02b) Is the consist kept in the correct location? (3.8 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.02b) La feuille de train est-elle conservée au bon emplacement ? (3.8 RTMD)

text.en: (3.02c) Is the carrier able to provide CANUTEC with a copy of the consist when the train is in operation or involved in an accident? (3.3(3) TDGR))
text.fr: (3.02c) Le transporteur est-il en mesure de fournir à CANUTEC une copie de la feuille de train lorsque le train est en service ou impliqué dans un accident? (3.3(3) RTMD)

text.en: (3.02d) Is the shipping document located in the appropriate place while the dangerous goods are stored in the course of transportation? (3.10 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.02d) Le document d'expédition est-il situé à lemplacement approprié pendant que les marchandises dangereuses sont entreposées au cours du transport? (3.10 RTMD)

text.en: (3.02e) Are shipping documents kept for two years? (s. 3.11 TDGR)
text.fr: (3.01e) Les documents d'expédition sont-ils conservés pendant deux ans ? (a. 3.11 RTMD)

text.en: (4.01) What type of MOC are you inspecting?
(4.01a) Are the labels present on the small MOC? (4.1, 4.4(1)(a), 4.5(a), 4.5(c), 4.10(3) TDGR)
(4.01b) Are the placards present on the large MOC? (4.1, 4.4(1)(b), 4.4(1)(c), 4.5(b), 4.5(c), 4.15.4(1) TDGR)
(4.01c) Are the labels or placards misleading? (4.2 TDGR)
(4.01d) Are the labels or placards visible, legible and the correct colour? (4.6 TDGR)
(4.01e) Are the labels or placards of the correct size and orientation? (4.7 TDGR)
(4.01f) Were the safety marks displayed on the large MOC before loading or packing occurred? (4.3 TDGR)
(4.01g) Is the correct primary class and subsidiary class label displayed on the small MOC? (4.10(1), 4.14, 4.22.1 TDGR)

(4.01h) Are the correct dangerous goods safety marks properly displayed on each side and on each end of the large or compartmentalized MOC? (4.15(1), 4.15.1, 4.16, 4.17(2), 4.18.1, 4.19, 4.20, 4.21 TDGR)
(4.01i) Is the shipping name and UN number properly displayed on the small MOC or tag (4.8(1), 4.11(1), 4.11(3), 4.12 TDGR)
(4.01j) Is the UN number properly displayed on the large MOC? (4.8(2), 4.15.2 TDGR)
(4.01k) Is the technical name displayed on the small MOC or a tag? (4.11(2), (3) TDGR)
(4.01l) Is the appropriate placard and markings displayed on the large MOC for UN1005 ANHYDROUS AMMONIA? (4.18.2 TDGR)
(4.01m) Is the marine pollutant mark displayed in accordance with subsection 4.22(1) of the TDGR?
(4.01n) Are the words "inhalation hazard" displayed in accordance with section 4.23 of the TDGR?
(4.01o) Is the lithium battery mark displayed in accordance with section 4.24 of the TDGR?
(4.01p) Does the overpack have the markings required by section 4.10.1 of the TDGR?
(4.01q) Does the consolidated bin have the markings required by section 4.10.2 of the TDGR?
(4.01r) Did the person change or remove the dangerous goods safety marks when the conditions that required the dangerous goods safety marks changed? (4.9 TDGR)
(5.01) Was the correct MOC selected to transport the dangerous goods? (5.1.1(1), 5.8, 5.10(1), 5.11, 5.12(1), 5.14(1), 5.16(1), 5.17, 5.18 TDGR)

(6.01) Is the person who handles, offers for transport, or transports dangerous goods have a training certificate or is supervised by a person who has a valid training certificate? (6.1, 6.5, 6.8 TDGR)
(6.01a) Does the training certificate contain all required information? (6.3(1), 6.3(2), 6.3(3), 6.5 TDGR)
(6.01b) Is the person who handles, offers for transport or transports dangerous goods adequately trained? (6.2 TDGR)
(6.02) Does the employer keep training records for at least two years? (6.6, 6.7 TDGR)
(7.01) Does the company require an ERAP for the dangerous goods they HOTI?
(7.01a) Does the company hold an approved ERAP for the dangerous goods they HOTI? (7.2(1) TDGR)
(7.01b) In response to a release or anticipated release of dangerous goods, did the person with an approved ERAP properly implement it? (7.8 TDGR)
(10.01) Does the company hold an equivalency, temporary or emergency certificate?
(10.01c) Is the company in compliance with their certificate?
(10.01d) Indicate the section(s) of the certificate related to the non-compliance.
Does the person have a training certificate?
Does the training certificate have all the required information?
